						               													<description>&amp;quot;Bid-It! is the bidding game where your hand doesn&amp;rsquo;t really matter, as long as you know how to bid it!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of Bid-It! is to bid how many of a given number appear on the cards held by all players together. For instance, a bid of &amp;ldquo;four 5&amp;rsquo;s&amp;rdquo; means the bidder believes that there are at least four fives being held by all players as a group. The next player must either make a higher bid or challenge the previous bid. Once a bid is challenged, the cards are revealed. If the bid was too high, the bidder loses a card. If not, the challenger loses a card. Players try to figure out each other&amp;rsquo;s hands by their bids, but remember, bluffing is not only legal, it&amp;rsquo;s sometimes quite effective (unless you get challenged!)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you&amp;rsquo;re very sure that your opponent&amp;rsquo;s bid was too high, why not bid &amp;ldquo;double&amp;rdquo; and put the loss of 2 cards on the line? Of course, the bidder may turn the tables on you and &amp;ldquo;redouble&amp;rdquo;. Or if you think that your opponent&amp;rsquo;s bid was exactly right, take a chance and bid &amp;ldquo;Perfecto!&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Includes 110 cards and instructions in a colorful metal tin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Inspired by Perudo&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
